qas.question: When did youtube enter a partnership with NBC?
What is the name of the section in youtube that allows major content publishers to post full length movies and episodes?
What was the intended purpose of youtube's "shows" section?
When did youtube launch the version of "shows" for the UK?
In 2010 how many movies did youtube's rental service offer?
Who entered into a partnership during June 2008 with NBC?

plausible_answers.text: MGM, Lions Gate Entertainment, and CBS

qas.question: Who did YouTube reach agreements with in November 2006?
What did YouTube launch in June 2009?
What did YouTube introduce in November 2010?

context: <b5_0>YouTube<b5_0/> entered into a marketing and advertising partnership with NBC in <a0_0>June 2006<a0_0/>. In November 2008, YouTube reached an agreement with <b6_0>MGM, Lions Gate Entertainment, and CBS<b6_0/>, allowing the companies to post full-length films and television episodes on the site, accompanied by advertisements in a section for US viewers called "<a1_0>Shows<a1_0/>". The move was intended <a2_0>to create competition<a2_0/> with websites such as Hulu, which features material from NBC, Fox, and Disney. <a3_0>In November 2009<a3_0/>, YouTube launched a version of <b7_0>"Shows" available to UK viewers<b7_0/>, offering around 4,000 full-length shows from more than 60 partners. In January 2010, YouTube introduced an <b8_0>online film rentals service<b8_0/>, which is available only to users in the US, Canada and the UK as of 2010. The service offers <a4_0>over 6,000 films<a4_0/>.
